    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "As decided together, we'll publish this as experimental release on the npm tag `experimental-typescript` to avoid potentially breaking users builds (stricter typecheck) while being able to let internal and external users to experiment with the generated typings.\r\n\r\nThis release will be handled manually at first (with instructions in the `CONTRIBUTING.md` file) and then will be automated with Ship.js.\r\n\r\nAdditionally to the standard release this experimental one will contains: \r\n* declaration files (generated with the `yarn build:types` command)\r\n* `types` entry in `package.json`\r\n\r\nThis PR will be updated accordingly.\r\n\r\nIn a separate PR, we will add an additional type check with `tsc` and the `allowJs` + `checkJs` flags to `true`. This will allows us to see the remaining errors in the JavaScript files and fix them progressively (by updating JSDoc or migrating JS files to TS). This check will be ran by the CI and will be allowed to fail.",
